<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=508&amp;p=3948#p3948"><![CDATA[
Well, it would require VRAM, for sure, and a huge portion of tiles that would fit the text that is displayed on the screen. Many RPG also had less detailed graphics than action games because of all tiles the letters takes, and I think this would be even worse.<br />Why would it need so much RAM ? Well, a lot of calculation should be done, effectively. This is common in SNES games because they have more RAM and PPU space used for tiles, and also has a faster CPU than the NES.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sat Aug 20, 2005 1:41 am</p><hr />
