<title type="html"><![CDATA[VWFs on the NES...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=508&amp;p=3936#p3936"><![CDATA[
Proportional fonts are more common in translations of games whose text engine supports kanji because efficient use of kanji seems to require a virtual bitmap, which means VRAM and not VROM. The Super NES had a lot more VRAM for a virtual bitmap on which to draw glyphs. It also had larger sprites and more sprites per scanline than the NES could ever dream of; a lot of games just drew text glyphs as sprites.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Aug 19, 2005 6:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
